  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2011-01-26",
    "date": "2011-02-19T15:43:00Z",
    "text": "Tax Code Termination Act - Terminates the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 after December 31, 2015, except for self-employment taxes, Federal Insurance Contributions Act (FICA)\u00a0taxes, and railroad retirement taxes. Requires a two-thirds majority vote in Congress to change such termination date.\n\nDeclares that any new federal tax system should be a simple and fair system that: (1) applies a low rate to all Americans; (2) provides tax relief for working Americans; (3) protects the rights of taxpayers and reduces tax collection abuses; (4) eliminates the bias against savings and investment; (5) promotes economic growth and job creation; and (6) does not penalize marriage or families.\n\nRequires that the new federal tax system be approved by Congress in its final form by July 4, 2015."
  },
